<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Walking the path of Knighthood</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Prophet">Prophet</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 8:26 p.m. 15/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Walking the path of Knighthood<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>I often sat and pondered things... my existence, the existence of the Gods and the ways of war. I meditated for hours on end, always coming up with the same thing" "Cogito ergo, sum."

<P>Yes, I think, therefore I am! However, am I evil or good? Righteous or a cur? Honorable or a scoundrel?
<P>Pondering these things gave me a bit of a headache so I went down to the local tavern and drank my weight in ale! In my drunken stupor that night, the images of three birds came to me. The first was the image of a great falcon. He soared on the wind and captured his prey in mid-air (surely a sign of the honorable - warrior)! The second was a dove... he sat nestled in his nest with other of his kind and was content ( a true sign of peace)! The third was the raven... black as night with a twinge of evil in his eye! Ah... not truly evil, more of a doing what must be done type.
<P>In this ale induced dream I saw the images of the three intertwine and become one. The awesome falcon, the peaceful nad honorable dove, and the evil raven! They combined to form the most magnificent bird I had ever seen!
<P>When I awoke, I knew my destiny. The destiny of a Shadow Knight. The honorable warrior who walks the fine line between peace and war; between love and hate; between mankind and the night.
<P>The next night, there was one final image I saw: There was a graven image of Desire; Painted with red blood on a ground of gold.
<P>My destiny lay with sword in hand...
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
